text: Baylor Strength Coach Brandon Washington Arrested on Prostitution Charge Vaughn Ridley/Getty Images Scott Polacek Featured Columnist February 7, 2017 Baylor Bears strength coach Brandon Washington was arrested Saturday morning on a charge of solicitation of prostitution, per Tommy Witherspoon of the Waco Tribune-Herald . While Witherspoon noted the Baylor athletics website didn't include any mention of Washington on Monday, McLennan County Sheriff Parnell McNamara said he was a strength coach at the school. According to a statement from the Baylor athletics department, Washington was an assistant in the football program at the time of his arrest.
